# ğŸ“˜ Sparse GCN + Transformer for Real-Time 3D & 2D-in-3D Human Pose Visualization

This repository contains a **hybrid Sparse Graph Convolution + Attention Transformer** framework for lifting 2D keypoints (from MediaPipe) into 3D, plus utilities to plot 2D poses in 3D space (flat Z=0) with bone-level labels. It includes training scripts, data-processing code, and inference scripts for static images and future video.

---

## âœ… Features

* **Sparse GCN + Transformer Model**
  â€¢ Takes normalized 2D (X,Y,0) inputs â†’ predicts 3D (X,Y,Z) joint positions.
  â€¢ Residual GCN blocks capture local graph structure; Transformer encodes global joint dependencies.

* **2D-in-3D Flat Plotting**
  â€¢ Embed a 2D pose into the plane Z=0.
  â€¢ Flip Y so image â€œupâ€ â†’ 3D â€œup.â€
  â€¢ Draw bones using MediaPipeâ€™s `POSE_CONNECTIONS`.

* **Bone-Level Classification**
  â€¢ Compute hip line from MediaPipe hips.
  â€¢ Color bones **red** (upper body), **blue** (lower body), **green** (torso).
  â€¢ Annotate bone midpoints and include a legend.

* **3D Pose Prediction & Alignment**
  â€¢ `PoseEstimator` (GCN+Transformer) lifts 2D â†’ 3D.
  â€¢ SolvePnP aligns predicted 3D with original image view.

* **Modular Visualization**
  â€¢ `visualize.py`: 2D overlay on image.
  â€¢ `plot_3d_skeleton.py`: upright 3D skeleton.
  â€¢ `plot_2d_in_3d_*.py`: flat Z=0 embeddings with optional bone labels.

* **Device-Agnostic**: Runs on CPU or GPU without code changes.

